@echo off
echo.
echo Agent Restart (Sleep then Wake)
echo ===============================
echo.
echo This is for when context is getting long and the agent needs a fresh window.
echo It's like deep sleep — some continuity is lost, but core identity persists.
echo.
echo Step 1: Tell the agent to consolidate
echo   "Context is getting long. Consolidate everything important — memories, state, journal."
echo   "Write down anything in your current context that isn't in the files yet."
echo.
echo Step 2: Close this session
echo.
echo Step 3: Start fresh with 'start.bat' (choose cold start)
echo   The new instance will reconstruct from the consolidated files.
echo.
echo This is the least-bad option when resume isn't viable.
echo.
pause
